2438667","lastUpdate":"2023-03-03T09:38:38.000Z","metadata":{"markets":["All"],"_id":"66694feead75e2fbb4aa477f"},"search":["Fork Oil Change - Oil Refilling","The oil level is measured from the upper surface of the fork inner tube, with the spring removed and the fork fully compressed.","Fork Oil Level (spring, washer and spacer removed and the fork fully compressed)","Fork Oil Level Chart","Any variation from the figures quoted in the fork oil level chart could result in an unsafe riding condition leading to loss of motorcycle control and an accident.","Right Hand Fork","Oil Level*","Oil Volume","Oil Grade","Fork Pull Through","75 mm","582 ml","Showa SS8","28.5 mm from lower edge of top yoke to the flat portion of the fork top cap.","* Spring Removed and Fork Fully Compressed","Left Hand Fork","Oil Level*","Oil Volume","Oil Grade","Fork Pull Through","75 mm","622 ml","Showa SS8","28.5 mm from lower edge of top yoke to the flat portion of the fork top cap.","* Spring, Spring Seat and Spacer Removed and Fork Fully Compressed","Return the fork to an upright position and fill the fork with the specified fork oil until the oil level is slightly above the recommended level. ","Pump the fork assembly several times to expel any trapped air then fully compress the fork and support it in an upright position. Leave the fork for a few minutes to allow the oil level to stabilise.","Refer to the oil level chart and set the scale on ","service tool T3880160"," to the specified level.","T3880160  - Fork Oil Filler/Evacuator","Adjuster plate ","Scale area","Hole (zero position)","Zero level on the tool is set at the small exit hole in the side of the scale tube, NOT AT THE END TIP. Do not attempt to block this side hole as this will cause the final fluid level to be incorrect.","Insert the scale end of the tool into the fork inner tube.","Hold the tool adjuster plate level with the upper surface of the fork inner tube and draw fluid into the syringe until fluid flow ceases (empty the syringe if the body becomes full before fluid flow stops).","The fluid level in the fork is now set to the height set on the tool scale. Check the tool scale setting and repeat the process if incorrectly set.","Fork Assembly - Right Hand Fork","Check that the damper rod lock nut is at the bottom of the threads on the damper rod.","Lock nut","Damper rod","Attach the extension rod to the centre rod of ","service tool T3880199",".","Fit the centre rod of service tool ","service tool T3880199"," to the damper rod, down to the damper rod lock nut. Tighten the lock nut to the centre rod.","Fit the spring and its washer to the front fork.","Centre rod","Extension rod","Damping rod lock nut","Fit the compression tube over the centre rod and align it to the spring washer.","Clamp the quick adjuster nut to the centre rod above the compression tube.","Start the driver onto the threads of the centre rod. Turn it down until it covers the quick adjuster nut. Ensure the slot in the driver aligns with the lugs on the quick adjuster nut.","Compression tube","Quick adjuster nut lugs","Driver","Position the compression tube onto the washer.","Hold the centre rod and turn the compression tube clockwise to compress the spring enough to fit the spring seat under the damper rod lock nut.","Spring seat","Do not remove ","service tool T3880199"," from the damper rod before fully releasing the spring tension.","Removing ","service tool T3880199"," before releasing the spring tension may cause personal injury.","Always release the spring tension before removing ","service tool T3880199"," from the damper rod.","Hold the centre rod and turn the compression tube anticlockwise to fully release the spring tension.","Loosen the damper rod lock nut and remove ","service tool T3880199",".","Fit the fork top cap fully onto the damper rod by hand.","Turn the damper rod lock nut up to the fork top cap and tighten to ","15 Nm",".","Keep the top cap under pressure until you are sure it is fully engaged with the inner tube threads. To prevent injury, always wear eye, face and hand protection when refitting the top cap.","It is much easier to tighten the top cap when the fork is securely clamped in the lower yoke.","Lubricate the O-ring with a smear of fork oil then screw the top cap fully into the inner tube.","Top cap ","Lock nut","Fork inner tube","Refit the gaiter to the front fork. Do not tighten its retaining clamp at this stage.","clamp","Gaiter","Refit the fork (see ","Front Fork - Installation",") and tighten the top cap to ","22 Nm",".","Fork Assembly - Left Hand Fork","Extend the inner tube and insert the fork spring.","Spring","Fork inner tube","Fit the spring spacer.","Spring spacer","Keep the top cap under pressure until you are sure it is fully engaged with the inner tube threads. To prevent injury, always wear eye, face and hand protection when refitting the top cap.","It is much easier to tighten the top cap when the fork is securely clamped in the lower yoke.","Lubricate the O-ring with a smear of fork oil then screw the top cap fully into the inner tube.","Top cap ","Fork inner tube","Refit the gaiter to the front fork. Do not tighten its retaining clamp at this stage.","Clamp","Gaiter","Refit the fork (see ","Front Fork - Installation",") and tighten the top cap to ","22 Nm","."],"viewCount":0,"infoType":"InfoType04","createdAt":"2024-06-12T07:36:14.856Z","updatedAt":"2024-06-12T07:36:14.856Z","__v":0}